    <section class="stats-labs" id="sect-00001">
<note id="fs-id1172804210713" class="statistics lab"><label/><title>Central Limit Theorem (Pocket Change)</title>

<para id="id48439801">Class Time: </para>
<para id="id48439812">Names:</para>


<list id="id48439824" list-type="bulleted">
<title>Student Learning Outcomes</title>
<item>The student will demonstrate and compare properties of the central limit theorem.</item>
</list>

<note id="id17413334">
<label/><title>NOTE</title>

<para id="fs-idm68262064">This lab works best when sampling from several classes and combining data.</para></note>

<list id="list-9099999888" list-type="enumerated"><title id="CollectData">Collect the Data</title><item>Count the change in your pocket. (Do not include bills.)</item>
<item>Randomly survey 30 classmates. Record the values of the change in <link target-id="Ch07_lab1_tbl001" document=""/>.
<table id="Ch07_lab1_tbl001" summary="Blank table with 30 empty cells.">
