</item>
	<item>Construct a histogram. Make five to six intervals. Sketch the graph using a ruler and pencil. Scale the axes.<newline/>
<figure class="scaled-down" id="id17573354"><media id="id17573359" alt="Blank graph template. The horizontal axis is labeled Value of the change and the vertical axis is labeled Frequency."><image src="../../media/fig-ch07_09_01.png" mime-type="image/png"/></media>
</figure></item>
<item> Calculate the following (<emphasis effect="italics">n</emphasis> = 1; surveying one person at a time):
<list id="list-975947" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha"><item><m:math>
 <m:mover accent="true">
  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
  <m:mo>¯</m:mo>
 </m:mover>

</m:math> = _______</item>
<item><emphasis effect="italics">s</emphasis> = _______</item>
</list></item>
<item>Draw a smooth curve through the tops of the bars of the histogram. Use one to two complete sentences to describe the general shape of the curve.</item>
</list><para id="element-509"><title>Collecting Averages of Pairs</title>Repeat steps one through five of the section <link target-id="CollectData" document="">Collect the Data.</link> with one exception. Instead of recording the change of 30 classmates, record the average change of 30 pairs.</para><list id="list-9759443" list-type="enumerated"><item>Randomly survey 30 <emphasis>pairs</emphasis> of classmates.</item>
<item>Record the values of the average of their change in <link target-id="Ch07_lab1_tbl002" document=""/>.
<table id="Ch07_lab1_tbl002" summary="Blank table containing 30 blank cells.">
