</list><list id="element-441" list-type="enumerated"><title>Discussion Questions</title><item>Why did the shape of the distribution of the data change, as <emphasis effect="italics">n</emphasis> changed? Use one to two complete sentences to explain what happened.</item>
<item>In the section titled <link target-id="CollectData" document="">Collect the Data</link>, what was the approximate distribution of the data? <emphasis effect="italics">X</emphasis> ~ _____(_____,_____)</item>
<item>In the section titled <link target-id="element-505436759" document="">Collecting Averages of Groups of Five</link>, what was the approximate distribution of the averages? <m:math>
 <m:mover accent="true">
  <m:mi>X</m:mi>
  <m:mo>¯</m:mo>
 </m:mover>

</m:math> ~ _____(_____,_____)</item>
<item>In one to two complete sentences, explain any differences in your answers to the previous two questions.</item></list></note>
<note id="fs-id1171897709330" class="statistics lab"><label/><title>Central Limit Theorem (Cookie Recipes)</title>

<para id="id5609695">Class Time: </para>
<para id="id5609702">Names:</para>

<list id="list-2397864897" list-type="bulleted">
<title>Student Learning Outcomes</title>
